```py
from models import base_models
import bittensor as bt
import httpx
import json
from typing import AsyncGenerator

POST_ENDPOINT = "generate_text"


async def stream_text_from_server(body: base_models.ChatIncoming, url: str):
    text_endpoint = url + POST_ENDPOINT
    full_text = ""
    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:  # noqa
        async with client.stream("POST", text_endpoint, json=body.dict()) as resp:
            async for chunk in resp.aiter_lines():
                try:
                    received_event_chunks = chunk.split("\n")
                    for event in received_event_chunks:
                        if event == "":
                            continue
                        prefix, _, data = event.partition(":")
                        if data.strip() == "[DONE]":
                            break
                        loaded_chunk = json.loads(data)
                        text = loaded_chunk["text"]
                        logprob = loaded_chunk["logprobs"][0]["logprob"]
                        data = json.dumps({"text": text, "logprob": logprob})
                        full_text += text

                        yield f"data: {data}\n\n"
                except Exception as e:
                    bt.logging.error(
                        f"Error in streaming text from the server: {e}. Original chunk: {chunk}"
                    )
    bt.logging.info(full_text)


async def chat_logic(body: base_models.ChatIncoming, url: str) -> AsyncGenerator:
    """Add gpu potential"""

    text_generator = stream_text_from_server(body, url)
    bt.logging.info(f"✅ About do some chatting, with model {body.model}✨")
    return text_generator
```

# Vision 4.0 

After 5 days of discussions and testing on testnet, we're releasing our official proposal, as well as a bunch of cool stuff. We're going full decentralisation, working our way to 1uid per entity, and making a proposal to the decentralised community for a protocol change - as is our role as the subnet owners.

Proposal: https://tauvision.ai/docs/proposal
📋 Changelog: https://tauvision.ai/docs/updates
Readme: https://tauvision.ai/docs/about
🔥 FAQ bot about the subnet 19 release, powered by subnet 19: https://tauvision.ai/release-bot  (it's in alpha, feedback welcome)
⛏️ Updated miner docs: https://tauvision.ai/docs/miner
📈 Stats page https://tauvision.ai/statistics/validators
💵 Miner dashboards: Releasing ASAP before release, final bugs being fixed (screenshot attached)

All the info is in the links above needed for the update - feel free to join the discussion about the update in the Corcel channel, https://discord.gg/wStKpm5z,  or in the thread below.

## Proposed date of update: 1pm UTC 13th June 2024

## Actions required

### Miners

**Proxy**
- Task configs will need to be defined, and then a restart of the proxy. 

**Workers**
Nothing (but turn off finetune to save costs)

### Validators

**Proxy**
Just a restart, will be handled by autoupdates

**Orchestrator / External server**
May require an update / reset to the latest image, will confirm on wednesday. 

PLEASE NOTE, ANY VALIDATORS STILL ON RUNPOD: It will soon be compulsory to use a gpu which is capable of docker-in-docker - i.e. not runpod / vast.

I know this is less convenient for some, but runpod & similar platforms are restricting our ability to grow to our full potential and power the ai world through decentralisation. Also, runpod is still facing the lots of issues with their a100's, and their support team is unable to resolve this as of yet.

Please please move over as soon as you can. The subnet 19 team is more than happy to assist with any external server setup and maintenance (no keys are required on the external server).

If you are one of these validators please contact me and we'll get you sorted 🙂 You can move over anytime before the update, or for a short while after - it will be compulsory from the update after this one
